{
  "texts": [
    "Another significant contribution comes from Udeshika Munasinghe et al. [13], who apply Bidirectional Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for estimating VaR in central counterparties.",
    "This methodology achieves a 20% reduction in estimation errors, outperforming conventional risk models.",
    "Furthermore, their custom GAN architectures enhance value-at-risk sensitivity measures by 22%, paving the way for more accurate and timely risk evaluations.",
    "These findings highlight the capacity of generative AI to bolster financial stability through innovative risk modeling.",
    "Karst's study [10] delves into the application of generative AI in banking, focusing on generating synthetic financial transaction data."
  ]
}